# Docs-First Implementation

When creating or modifying source or test files mapped in `docs/traceability.json`:

## Source files

- Add or preserve a file-level or construct-level comment citing the `REQ-*` being implemented.
- Cited REQ IDs MUST exist in the matching feature README under `docs/features/<feature>/`.
- Do not implement behavior that has no corresponding REQ — add the REQ to the spec first.

Example (TypeScript):

```typescript
/**
 * REQ-PLATFORM-INFRA-003 — Static site via S3 and CloudFront.
 */
export class StaticSiteService { ... }
```

## Test files

- Every test file MUST contain at least one `Traceability:` comment referencing `AC-*` or `REQ-*`.
- Tests should map to acceptance criteria from the feature README.

Example:

```typescript
// Traceability: AC-PLATFORM-INFRA-004 (REQ-PLATFORM-INFRA-004)
test("synth creates EnliveFunPublicProd stack", () => { ... });
```

## After editing

Run `/docs-audit` and fix all BLOCKER findings before finishing.
